      "description": "Presenting a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46). This example features the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, delivering 333 hp through six individual throttle bodies and a crisp 6-speed manual gearbox. The power is managed by a factory M-Variable differential lock, ensuring optimal torque distribution across the rear axle. This chassis remains communicative and composed, benefitting from a recent suspension refresh with Bilstein dampers. While showing honest signs of use consistent with its history, the mechanical vitals are strong; the VANOS system has been serviced, and the rear subframe has been inspected for structural integrity. An ideal specimen for the purist seeking the analog feedback of a peak-era M-car.",
